<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n15029h"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n15" href="#n15029h">N15 (VI.D.2)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n15all.htm#n15029h"> 29(h)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Thorstein the Red</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Ari was born in the year 1067, and his ancestry was sufficiently distinguished to encourage any natural tendency in his mind to a study of the past. On his father&apos;s side he was a descendant of &Oacute;laf the White, who in the latter half of the ninth century was Norse king in Dublin. &Oacute;laf&apos;s son, <mark>Thorstein the Red</mark>, made a league with Earl Sigurd of the Orkneys against the Scots <small> W. A. Craige, <a name="ICEL" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#ICEL"><cite title="source">The Icelandic Sagas</cite></a>, (1913) 21</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c15205h" href="c15all.htm#c15205h">VI.C.15:205(h)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
